Day 1: HTML Fundamentals

Today you'll learn the basic structure of an HTML page and the most commonly used tags.

1. What is HTML?

HTML (HyperText Markup Language) is used to create the structure of web pages.

Think of HTML as the skeleton of a website.

Example:

<h1>Welcome</h1>
<p>This is my first webpage.</p>
2. Basic HTML Document Structure

Every HTML page starts with:

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
    <title>My First Page</title>
</head>
<body>

    <h1>Hello World!</h1>
    <p>Welcome to HTML.</p>

</body>
</html>
Explanation
Tag	Purpose
<!DOCTYPE html>	Tells browser this is HTML5
<html>	Root element
<head>	Contains page information
<title>	Browser tab title
<body>	Visible content
3. Headings

HTML provides 6 heading levels.

<h1>Main Heading</h1>
<h2>Sub Heading</h2>
<h3>Section Heading</h3>
<h4>Smaller Heading</h4>
<h5>Very Small Heading</h5>
<h6>Smallest Heading</h6>
Important

Use only one h1 per page whenever possible.

4. Paragraph Tag
<p>This is a paragraph.</p>

Example:

<p>I am learning HTML.</p>
<p>HTML is easy to learn.</p>
5. Line Break

Move content to the next line.

Hello<br>
World

Output:

Hello
World
6. Horizontal Line
<hr>

Example:

<h1>About Me</h1>
<hr>
<p>I am a Java Developer.</p>
7. Comments

Comments are ignored by browsers.

<!-- This is a comment -->

Example:

<!-- Header Section -->
<h1>Welcome</h1>
8. Create Your First HTML Page

Create a file named:

index.html

Add:

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
    <title>My Profile</title>
</head>
<body>

    <h1>Priyadharshini</h1>

    <hr>

    <p>I am learning HTML.</p>

    <p>I work as a Java Developer.</p>

</body>
</html>

Open it in your browser.

Day 1 Practice Task

Create a page with:

Your name using h1
Your designation using h2
Two paragraphs about yourself
One horizontal line
One comment

Expected structure:

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
    <title>About Me</title>
</head>
<body>

    <!-- My Introduction -->

    <h1>Your Name</h1>

    <h2>Java Developer</h2>

    <hr>

    <p>Paragraph 1</p>

    <p>Paragraph 2</p>

</body>
</html>
